The paper proposes a system for classification of source printer from scanned images of printed documents using local texture patterns based features and a single classifier. This involves image processing techniques and machine learning algorithms, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research. The paper also deals with issues related to forgery and copyright infringement, which are relevant to computer security (cs.CR) research. Additionally, the paper involves analysis of printed letters and fonts, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper uses machine learning algorithms for classification, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) research.
